The paper proposes a method for autonomous exploration using a theory of robustness based on Probabilistic Metric Temporal Logic (P-MTL) for offline verification and online control of hybrid systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses Markov Chain Monte Carlo, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Control Systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves optimization, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, and cs.CV.
